
TY  - JOUR
T1  - Functions of Parting CEremonies in Dying Organizations
AU  - Harris, Stanley G.
AU  - Sutton, Robert I.
Y1  - 1986/03/01
PY  - 1986
DA  - 1986/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255857
DO  - 10.5465/255857
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 5
EP  - 30
VL  - 29
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This paper advances a theory about the functions that parting ceremonies serve for members displaced by organizational deaths. The theory is grounded in data from 11 parties, picnics, and dinners that occurred in six dying organizations. We propose that parting ceremonies create settings in which people can exchange emotional support and can edit self-, social system, and event schemata. We also assert that such gatherings provide opportunities for managers to influence the course of organizational demise.
AB  - This paper advances a theory about the functions that parting ceremonies serve for members displaced by organizational deaths. The theory is grounded in data from 11 parties, picnics, and dinners that occurred in six dying organizations. We propose that parting ceremonies create settings in which people can exchange emotional support and can edit self-, social system, and event schemata. We also assert that such gatherings provide opportunities for managers to influence the course of organizational demise.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/255857
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/255857
